{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection\/subscript(safe:)"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Index"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":"? { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"index","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The position of the element to access."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"range simply result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Example usage:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Accesses the element at the specified position in a safe manner.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"constraints":[{"code":"Self","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Collection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}]},"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftExtras","relatedModules":["Swift"]}],"roleHeading":"I